```
`frame.pin()` increments the pin count.

So, when a worker starts using a frame, pin count goes from 1 to 2. When the frame is replaced in `TimelineLedger`, `cool()` is called, pin count goes from 2 to 1. When the worker moves to a new frame, `cursor.close()` is called, which calls `frame.unpin()`, pin count goes from 1 to 0. Since `cooled` is true, `closeLoadedGeneration()` is called. This all seems correct!

