The `PluginModuleFactory` instance is created from the `classLoader`. Does it keep a reference to the class loader? Yes, `factory.getClass().getClassLoader()` is the `URLClassLoader`. And `factory.open()` returns a `PluginModule`. If that `PluginModule` is also a class loaded by the same `URLClassLoader` (which it is, `CustomerPluginModule`), then the `LoadedGeneration` holds a reference to the `PluginModule`, which holds a reference to its class, which holds a reference to the `URLClassLoader`.

